description: The molecule is a hydroperoxy fatty acid that is (14S,15R)-epoxy-(5Z,8Z,10E)-icosatrienoic acid in which the hydroperoxy group is located at position 12S. answer: The molecule is an organic heterotetracyclic compound that is obtained by methoxylation of wortmannin. It has a role as an EC 2.7.1.137 (phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase) inhibitor. It is an organic heterotetracyclic compound, a delta-lactone, an acetate ester and a methyl ether. It derives from a wortmannin.

description: The molecule is a member of the class of cyclopentanols carrying 1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl and 4-chlorobenzylidene and geminal dimethyl substituents at positions 1, 2 and 5 respectively. answer: The molecule is a member of the class of cyclohexanols carrying 1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl, 4-chlorophenyl and geminal dimethyl substituents at positions 1, 2 and 5 respectively. Used to control a range of fungal infections in fruit, vegetables, and cereals. It has a role as an EC 1.14.13.70 (sterol 14alpha-demethylase) inhibitor and an antifungal agrochemical. It is a member of cyclohexanols, a member of monochlorobenzenes, a tertiary alcohol, a member of triazoles, a conazole fungicide, and a triazole fungicide.

description: The molecule is an anionic phospholipid that is the conjugate base of beta-D-mannosyl C32-phosphomycoketide obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3. It derives from a phosphomycoketide C32(2-). It is a conjugate base of a beta-D-mannosyl C32-phosphomycoketide.
answer: Molecular Description: The molecule is an alpha-D-galactosyl-1-phosphate which is bound to a long-chain alcohol containing several methyl-branching groups. It is a complex glycosyl polyprenol phosphate involved in lipid-linked oligosaccharide biosynthesis pathways such as in the process of N-glycosylation. It is a type of polyprenol phosphate with a significant role in cellular biology, functioning as a lipid carrier molecule in glycoprotein biosynthesis.

description: The molecule is a member of the class of tetracenomycins that is 8-demethyltetracenomycin C in which the hydroxyl hydrogens at position 8 and 10 a are replaced by a 2,3,4-tri-O-methyl-alpha-L-rhamnosyl and methyl groups respectively. answer: The molecule is a tetracenomycins that is tetracenomycin C in which the hydroxyl hydrogen at position 8 is replaced by an alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue, and each hydroxy group of the rhamnose is methylated forming rhamnosyl hexamethyl ether. It is a tetracenomycin, a methyl ether, an enone, an alpha-L-rhamnoside, a monosaccharide derivative, a methyl ester, a cyclic ketone and a tertiary alpha-hydroxy ketone. description: The molecule is a cyclic peptide antibiotic produced by a strain of Streptomyces toyocaensis. It has a role as a fungal metabolite. description: The molecule is a monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted at position 3 by a nonaprenyl group. It is a monohydroxybenzoic acid and an olefinic compound. It is a conjugate acid of a 4-hydroxy-3-all-trans-nonaprenylbenzoate.

answer: Molecular Description: The molecule is an elemental trivalent cation of samarium. Samarium is a lanthanide with atomic number 62. The trivalent state, [Sm+3], is commonly found in compounds and solutions.

It appears to result from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with a carboxylate-containing fatty acid. It is associated with a triphosphate nucleotide structure, indicating a linkage similar to that found in CoA derivatives. description: The molecule is a secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 5-{[(5-tert-butyl-1,3-oxazol-2-yl)methyl]sulfanyl}-1,3-thiazol-2-amine. It has a role as an H1-receptor antagonist, an antihistamine, and a vasodilator agent. It is also known for its sedative properties. It is an aromatic amine, a member of imidazolines, and a phenol.

description: The molecule is a hydrate obtained by combining oxyphenbutazone with one molar equivalent of water. Commonly used to treat pain, swelling and stiffness associated with arthritis and gout, it was withdrawn from the market 1984 following association with blood dyscrasis and Stevens-Johnson syndrome. It has a role as a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug, a non-narcotic analgesic, a gout suppressant, an antipyretic, an antimicrobial agent and an antineoplastic agent. It contains an oxyphenbutazone.
answer: The molecule is a compound in which the core structure is that of a phenylbutazone hydroxylated at the para position on one of the phenyl rings and is present as a monohydrate. This hydroxylated derivative of phenylbutazone is often used to study the effects of phenylbutazone metabolites. It is known for its roles as a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug, a non-narcotic analgesic, and an antipyretic agent. The compound is also regarded as a xenobiotic metabolite as it provides insights into the metabolites of phenylbutazone. It is a member of pyrazolidines and phenols, derived from phenylbutazone.

description: The molecule is a non-proteinogenc L-alpha-amino acid that is L-alpha-aminobutyric acid in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal methyl group has been replaced by a dihydroxy(oxido)-lambda(5)-phosphanyl group. It is a phosphoamino acid derivative and a L-alpha-amino acid anion. It is a conjugate base of an L-seryl phosphate(2-).

description: The molecule is the L-alpha-amino acid that is N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine linked via an alpha glycosidic bond to the O at position 3 of L-serine. It is a L-serine derivative and a non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid.

Cholic acid plays several biological roles, including acting as a human metabolite, a mouse metabolite, a gastric acidifier, and a colligenic agent. answer: The molecule is a tetraanion of (2E,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z,25Z)-octacosaheptaenoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions; principal microspecies at pH 7.3. It is an ultra-long-chain fatty acyl-CoA and an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA. It is a conjugate base of a (2E,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z,25Z)-octacosaheptaenoyl-CoA.

description: The molecule is a 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of 2-hydroxydodecanoic acid. The major microspecies at pH 7.3 It derives from a dodecanoate. It is a conjugate base of a 2-hydroxydodecanoic acid.
answer: Molecular Description: The molecule is a long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of dodecanoic acid (lauric acid), obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group. It has a role as a human metabolite and an algal metabolite. It is a conjugate base of a dodecanoic acid.

description: The molecule is an aci-nitro compound resulting from the formal oxidation of the oxime nitrogen of an omega-(methylsulfany)-(E)-alkanal oxime. It is an aci-nitro compound and a methyl sulfide. It derives from an omega-(methylsulfanyl)-(E)-alkanal oxime.
answer: The molecule is a member of the class of nitroso compounds that is 3-sulfanylpropyl nitrosothiol. It is a nitroso compound and a thio compound. It has a role as a metabolite.

description: The molecule is a lactone, a C19-gibberellin and a gibberellin monocarboxylic acid. It is a conjugate acid of a gibberellin A34(1-).
answer: The molecule is a C19-gibberellin, initially identified in Pisum sativum. It differs from gibberellin A1 by having an additional beta-OH group at C-2 (gibbane numbering). It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is a C19-gibberellin, a lactone, and a gibberellin monocarboxylic acid.

description: The molecule is an N-acyl-1-O-beta-D-glucosyl-4-hydroxy-15-methylhexadecasphinganine in which the acyl group has 18 carbons and 0 double bonds. It derives from a 15-methylhexadecaphytosphingosine.
answer: The molecule is a 1-O-acyl-21-O-acyl-23-hydroxy tetracosasphinganine glycoside where the sugar moiety is beta-D-galactopyranose and the ceramide backbone is derivatized with a hydroxyl group at position 23. It is a sphingolipid and a glycosphingolipid. It derives from a beta-D-galactopyranose. It has roles as a metabolite and an antigen.

description: The molecule is a primary fatty amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (9Z)-hexadecenoic acid with ammonia. It has a role as a fungal metabolite and a human metabolite. It derives from a palmitoleic acid.
answer: The molecule is a primary fatty acid amide that is tridec-9-enamide. It is a long-chain primary fatty amide and is derived from a tridec-9-enoic acid.

description: The molecule is the fundamental parent of a class of sesquiterpenes with a structure based upon a cyclodecane ring substituted with an isopropyl and two methyl groups. It is a terpenoid fundamental parent and a sesquiterpene.
answer: The molecule is a terpenoid hydrocarbon specifically identified as (+)-sativene. It is a monocyclic sesquiterpene featuring two isopropyl groups and one methyl group attached to a cyclodecane backbone. It is naturally occurring and has been characterized in certain essential oils.

description: The molecule is a guaiacyl lignin obtained by cyclodimerisation of coniferol. It has a role as a plant metabolite and an anti-inflammatory agent. It is a member of 1-benzofurans, a primary alcohol, a guaiacyl lignin and a member of guaiacols. It derives from a coniferol.
answer: The molecule is a dehydrodiconiferyl alcohol that has (2S,3R)-configuration. It is a natural product isolated from several plant species including Aglaia foveolata, Viburnum erosum, and Rosa multiflora. It has a role as a plant metabolite. It is an enantiomer of a (-)-dehydrodiconiferyl alcohol.

description: The molecule is an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid. It is a long-chain fatty acyl-CoA and an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA. It derives from an 8,9-EET. It is a conjugate acid of an 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl-CoA(4-).
answer: The molecule is an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid. It is a long-chain fatty acyl-CoA and an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA. It derives from an 8,9-EET. It is a conjugate acid of an 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl-CoA(4-).

description: The molecule is an alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-D-GlcNAc where the glucosamine at the reducing end has beta-configuration at its anomeric centre. It has a role as an epitope.
answer: The molecule is a branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine at the reducing end having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at the 3-position, and an alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 4-position. It has a role as an antigen. It is an amino tetrasaccharide and a glucosamine oligosaccharide.

description: The molecule is a Glu-Cys-Gly tripeptide derivative of glutathione containing a 2-hydroxyethyl substituent on the S of the Cys residue. It derives from a glutathione.
answer: The molecule is a tripeptide consisting of L-aspartic acid, L-cysteine and L-homoserine residues joined in sequence by peptide linkages. It has a role as a human metabolite. It is a tripeptide and a thiol-containing compound. It is a conjugate acid of a tripeptide anion.

description: The molecule is a pyrrolopyrimidine that is 7-methyl-7H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidin-4-amine which has been substituted at position 5 by a 4-fluoro-2,3-dihydro-1H-indol-5-yl group, the nitrogen of which has been acylated by a (6-methylpyridin-2-yl)acetyl group. An orally bioavailable PERK inhibitor. It has a role as an EC 3.1.3.48 (protein-tyrosine-phosphatase) inhibitor, a PERK inhibitor and an antineoplastic agent. It is a pyrrolopyrimidine, a biaryl, a member of indoles, a member of methylpyridines, an organofluorine compound and a tertiary carboxamide.
answer: The molecule is a member of the class of isoquinolines that is 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline substituted at N-2 with a 4-(3-methyl-1H-pyrazol-4-yl)pyrimidin-2-yl group, at C-5 with a fluorophenyl group, and at N-1 with an acetyl group. It has a role as a TGF-betaRI kinase inhibitor. It is a member of isoquinolines, an N-acylamino compound, an aromatic amine, a tertiary carboxamide, and a member of monochlorobenzenes.
